      "content": "okay, so the cap is on the rate, not the payment. that sounds pretty risky if the interest rate goes up even a little bit. is it common for these rates to be really erratic or jump around a lot suddenly? like, how much \"chaos\" should i actually expect when it comes to these adjustments?",
